TITLE: Ex-NFL star Drew Bledsoe rips Tony Romo for how he handled taking Cowboys job: 'Had all the answers'
SUMMARY: Former Dallas Cowboys quarterback Drew Bledsoe ripped Tony Romo for how he allegedly handled taking over as the starter in 2006. Bledsoe made his remarks on ESPN.

TITLE: Kentucky police recover SUV, AR-15 in manhunt for I-75 shooter
SUMMARY: Kentucky police have recovered an SUV and AR-15 rifle in the manhunt for a suspected gunman who is accused of opening fire near Interstate 75, injuring several people.

TITLE: DOJ: Illegal immigrant stole US citizen's identity to vote in multiple elections, obtain American passport
SUMMARY: An undocumented immigrant from Guatemala who allegedly fraudulently registered to vote in Alabama and voted in 2016 and 2020 elections is to plead guilty.

TITLE: Colts' Anthony Richardson tosses sublime 60-yard TD pass, dazzles NFL fans
SUMMARY: Indianapolis Colts quarterback Anthony Richardson threw a dazzling 60-yard touchdown pass to Alec Pierce against the Houston Texans Sunday.

TITLE: 'The Last Showgirl' star Pamela Anderson says being 'underestimated' her entire career has had it advantages
SUMMARY: Pamela Anderson is opening up about being overlooked and "underestimated" by Hollywood and saying why it's given her an advantage in her next role.

TITLE: Silicon Valley investor says Elon Musk should be prosecuted for 'undermining govt. that's paying him'
SUMMARY: Silicon Valley investor Roger McNamee argued that Elon Musk's free speech should be curtailed because of the government ties to his businesses like SpaceX.

TITLE: Nikki Haley breaks with Trump on IVF proposal, still says she's 'on standby' for campaign
SUMMARY: Nikki Haley said she does not support Donald Trump's policy proposal to mandate the government or insurance companies cover IVF treatment.

TITLE: Meta claims another 'error' after conservative college's second complaint about Facebook treatment
SUMMARY: Hillsdale College claims Facebook wrongly gave users a warning when searching for its online courses page, which parent company Meta says was an "error."

TITLE: Alzheimer’s risk may increase with light pollution, new study finds
SUMMARY: Exposure to outdoor light at night could put people at a higher risk of developing Alzheimer’s disease, according to a new study published in Frontiers in Neuroscience.

TITLE: NFL legend Tom Brady eager to call Cowboys-Browns Week 1 game: 'Let's go'
SUMMARY: Tom Brady appeared on "FOX NFL Sunday" before the slate of games opened up. He said he was ready to call his first game later in the day.

TITLE: A second Trump presidency has the UN fearing for its future, employee caught on camera reveals
SUMMARY: During his first term as President Donald Trump took a no-nonsense approach to the United Nations and pushed back against much of the world body's anti-America moves.

TITLE: Sen. John Fetterman makes prediction for Trump and Harris debate: ‘It's going to be close’
SUMMARY: Pennsylvania Sen. John Fetterman on Sunday said he believes that both former President Trump and Vice President Harris will perform well during the upcoming debate.

TITLE: Trump campaign adviser tears into VP Harris: She can 'run' but she can't 'hide' from Biden's record
SUMMARY: Trump campaign adviser Corey Lewandowski called out Vice President Kamala Harris' apparent flip-flops on key issues while facing questions about Trump's alleged shift toward the center.

TITLE: Diondre Overton, national champion wide receiver for Clemson, dead at 26
SUMMARY: Former Clemson Tigers wide receiver Diondre Overton, who won two titles with the team, has died, the school announced Saturday. He was 26.

TITLE: Jennifer Aniston's regimented workout routine includes functional fitness training with at-home equipment
SUMMARY: Jennifer Aniston incorporates Pvolve, functional fitness training, into her weekly routine to keep up with her physical health. Rachel Katzman is the founder of Pvolve.

TITLE: Kendrick Lamar headlines Super Bowl LIX's halftime show
SUMMARY: Kendrick Lamar was named the Super Bowl LIX halftime performer on Sunday -- right before the 2024 season's first Sunday slate was set to get underway.

TITLE: Bernie Sanders says Harris dropping far-left policies 'in order to win the election'
SUMMARY: Progressive Sen. Bernie Sanders told NBC that Kamala Harris was being "pragmatic" by dropping her far-left policies "in order to win the election."

TITLE: Orlando Bloom thought he 'was gonna die' from 52-pound weight loss for new movie
SUMMARY: For his role in the movie, "The Cut," Orlando Bloom says he lost nearly one-third of his body weight. The English actor added that he thought he "was gonna die."

TITLE: Voters report Kamala Harris is more radical than Trump: 'too liberal or progressive'
SUMMARY: Voters reported in a new New York Times/Sienna College poll that Vice President Harris is viewed as "too liberal" more than former President Trump is considered "too conservative."

TITLE: Steelers tap Justin Fields as starting quarterback vs Falcons as Russell Wilson deals with injury
SUMMARY: Pittsburgh Steelers quarterback Justin Fields will start Sunday's game against the Atlanta Falcons as Russell Wilson recovers from a calf issue.

TITLE: Dak Prescott, Cowboys agree to historic contract extension before kickoff: reports
SUMMARY: Dallas Cowboys star quarterback Dak Prescott reportedly agreed to a massive contract extentsion that will make him the highest-paid player in NFL history.

TITLE: Trump campaign slams report 'radical' Keith Ellison is on Harris' AG short list: 'natural fit'
SUMMARY: The Trump campaign slammed a report that Minnesota AG Keith Ellison is on VP Kamala Harris' short list for potential candidates for U.S. attorney general, which Ellison has denied.

TITLE: New poll shows Trump holds lead with ‘remarkably resilient’ support
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump has maintained his national lead over Vice President Kamala Harris despite a surge in enthusiasm for the Democratic ticket in recent weeks.

TITLE: Bloodthirsty Venezuelan street gang sparks fear in US amid migrant surge: What to know
SUMMARY: The violent street gang known as Tren de Aragua has been making advances throughout the United States and drawing national attention in the process.

TITLE: Kentucky police resume manhunt for gunman in I-75 shooting
SUMMARY: Joseph A. Couch, 32, was named a person of interest in the Kentucky shooting, and authorities have said he should be considered armed and dangerous.
